Good morning,

This Stratechery interview is another installment of the Stratechery Founde=
r series; as a reminder, one of the challenges in covering startups is the =
lack of available data. My solution is to go in the opposite direction and =
interview founders directly, letting them give their subjective overview of=
 their companies, while pressing them on their business model, background, =
and long-term potential.

Today=E2=80=99s Stratechery Interview is with Tailscale ( https://tailscale=
.com/ ) Co-Founder and CEO Avery ( https://x.com/apenwarr ) Pennarun ( http=
s://bsky.app/profile/apenwarr.ca ). Tailscale is a peer-to-peer VPN with bu=
ilt-in encryption, authentication, and network traversal management; that s=
ounds complicated, but in fact using Tailscale is incredibly easy. I person=
ally am a long-time user and fan, and was very excited to conduct this Inte=
rview for not just professional reasons but personal ones as well. I=E2=80=
=99m also not the only happy user: Tailscale recently surpassed 10,000 busi=
ness customers ( https://tailscale.com/blog/welcome-grace-lin-10000-custome=
rs ) and has over 500,000 weekly active users ( https://betakit.com/tailsca=
le-hits-10000-paid-business-clients-after-doubling-customer-base-in-past-10=
-months/ ) , with a total active userbase in the millions.

What was so interesting about this interview is how nearly every feature th=
at I love about Tailscale has a connection to Pennarun=E2=80=99s background=
. In this interview we discuss creating a home network as a child, building=
 a Linux driver as a teenager, and starting a company to help small busines=
ses share a dial-up connection as a college student. We then dive into Penn=
arun=E2=80=99s professional experience with a Canadian bank and Google (and=
 back again), and how that led to both the Tailscale concept and its name. =
We also get into Tailscale the company, how its model is disruptive, and wh=
y Pennarun sees great potential in keeping it that way.

As a reminder, all Stratechery content, including interviews, is available =
as a podcast; click the link at the top of this email to add Stratechery to=
 your podcast player.

On to the Interview:

An Interview with Tailscale Co-Founder and CEO Avery Pennarun
-------------------------------------------------------------

